<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF893528E0FF2AAFDF9FD19FD62" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147326" collectorName="J. Serrano" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
The specimen here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793528E0FF02FFDF9FDA8FD4E" box="[530,633,619,645]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a female, labelled “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF14AFDF9FC17FD4F" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[887,966,619,644]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF14AFDF9FC17FD4F" box="[887,966,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mi. in Gal. mer.” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793528E0FF6F3FDF9FA90FD4E" box="[1230,1345,619,645]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">Lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF75AFDF9FE04FD62" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF75AFDF9FEE9FD63" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">Acupalpus atratus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493528E0FF302FD1DFE04FD62" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[319,469,655,681]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="2687537393528E0FF075FD1DFD6FFD62" box="[584,702,655,681]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E93528E0FF2FAFD21FF2EFC4A" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593528E0FF2FAFD21FA49FCF2" blockId="11.[151,1436,619,897]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">
This name is currently considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF0C4FD21FBE4FD06" authority="(Sturm, 1825)" baseAuthorityName="Sturm" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[761,1077,690,717]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunnipes">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF0C4FD21FC5AFD06" box="[761,907,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">A. brunnipes</emphasis>
(Sturm, 1825)
</taxonomicName>
, a species that is mentioned by Dejean himself (1829) in the original description. It is a species readily recognized by the lack of a dorsal pore in the second half of the third interval of elytra, a character that is noted in the 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793528E0FF1E6FD69FB93FCDE" box="[987,1090,763,789]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF658FD69FB03FCDF" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[1125,1234,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF658FD69FB03FCDF" box="[1125,1234,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">A. atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and that was also mentioned by Dejean. Keys to identify 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF06DFC8DFD0EFCF2" baseAuthorityName="Sturm" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[592,735,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunnipes">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF06DFC8DFD0EFCF2" box="[592,735,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">A. brunnipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are found elsewhere (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493528E0FF1EBFC8DFBA4FCF2" author="Jeannel, R." box="[982,1141,799,825]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" pagination="572 - 1173" refId="ref11231" refString="Jeannel, R. (1942) Coleopteres carabiques. Deuxieme partie. Faune de France 40. Librairie de la Faculte des Sciences, Paris, pp. 572 - 1173." type="book chapter" year="1942">Jeannel, 1942</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493528E0FF6BDFC8DFAC1FCF2" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[1152,1296,799,825]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" pagination="344 - 386" refId="ref12516" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2004) Harpalina. In: Freude, H., Harde, K. W., Lohse, G. A. &amp; Klausnitzer, B. (Eds.), Die Kafer Mitteleuropas. Bd. 2 Adephaga 1: Carabidae (Laufkafer). Spektrum-Verlag, Heidelberg / Berlin, pp. 344 - 386." type="book chapter" year="2004">Wrase, 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493528E0FF726FC8DFA84FCF2" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[1307,1365,799,825]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" refId="ref12634" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2011) Genus Tschitscherinellus. Arndt, E., Schnitter, P., Sfenthourakis, S. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (Eds.), Ground beetles (Carabidae) of Greece. Pensoft, Sofia, pp. 163." type="book" year="2011">2011</bibRefCitation>
, etc.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593528E0FF2FAFCD1FF2EFC4A" blockId="11.[151,1436,619,897]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">
The species is distributed in the Azores, Central Europe, the Mediterranean Basin (but not in the Levant) and 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593528E0FF2AAFCF5FF2AFC4A" box="[151,251,871,897]" name="Turkey" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
